ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000ICPpv:ref

What is the impact of the issue on your business?
With the temp storage filling up the hard drive the database team gets alerted and tickets are automatically opened about the drive being full. They are hesitant to expand the drive because it appears to just be temp files and they want to make sure there isn’t something improperly configured.
Who is affected by this issue?
The database team and then us when they reach out asking why the drive is full
What steps to troubleshoot the issue have already been taken?
None because I don’t know if this is expected behavior or not as I have little knowledge of how the database part is ran.
What are you trying to do or accomplish?
Verify if the temporarily files from our scans are expected to take up as much space as they are.
Is this a new configuration, data collection or report?
No
If no, has anything changed in your environment since the last time it worked?
Not that I’m aware if.
When did this issue start?
It’s been ongoing where periodically I’ll be notified about it. Not sure when it started
What are the steps to reproduce?
I’m not sure what triggers it other than typically it’s scanning file servers and AD when it happens.

Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

Hi William,

461 GB for the tempDB is actually about the mid range of what we see for the temp DB size.

You may need to adjust the size based on our documentation. We can give some rough numbers in the below document based on what modules you are using.
If you look under the heading "RAM, CPU, and Disk Space " you will see the various modules, and inside these documents will give estimates on how much space you may need in tempDB.

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Requirements/Overview.htm
